### Static Equilibrium for Rigid Extended Bodies

Equilibrium is a concept to describe the state of a body that is either at rest or moving at a constant velocity. The conditions for equilibrium are the same, regardless whether the body is at rest or moving at a constant velocity. However, if the body is at rest, we say that the body is in _static_ equilibrium.

**Conditions for (Static) Equilibrium of a rigid extended body:**

**The net external force acting on the body is zero.** \(\Sigma F_{ext}=0\).

**The net moment on the body _about any point_ is zero.** \(\Sigma\tau=0\).

