### Three-Force Systems

A solid body submitted to three forces whose lines of action are not parallel is in equilibrium, if the following three conditions apply:

1. The lines of action are coplanar (\(\Rightarrow\) all forces lie in one and the same plane)

2. The vector sum of the forces is equal to the zero vector (\(\Rightarrow\) they can form a closed vector triangle)

3. The lines of action are _convergent_ (\(\Rightarrow\) their lines of action cross through a single point).

